mines these new collaborations, where the distinctions between Hollywood’s “dream factory” and Xi Jinping's ";Chinese Dream"; of global influence become increasingly blurred. With insightful policy analysis, ethnographic research, and interviews with CEOs, directors, and film workers in Beijing, Shanghai, and Los Angeles, Aynne Kokas offers an unflinching look at China’s new role in the global media industries. A window into the partnerships with Chinese corporations that now shape Hollywood, this book will captivate anyone who consumes commercial media in the twenty-first century.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aMass media and globalization. 0aMass mediazChina. 0aMass mediazUnited States. 0aMotion pictureszChina. 0aMotion pictureszUnited States. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / Film & Video / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2017z978311066755440uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052096729840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520967298423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520967298/original  a978-3-11-066755-4  University of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2017b2017  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles